quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  19,65,"Lord of the Heavens and of the Earth, and of all that is between them! Worship Him, then, and abide thou steadfast in his worship. Knowest thou any other of the same name"
  19,66,"Man saith: \"What! after I am dead, shall I in the end be brought forth alive"
  19,67,"Doth not man bear in mind that we made him at first, when he was nought"
  19,68,"And I swear by thy Lord, we will surely gather together them and the Satans: then will we set them on their knees round Hell"
  19,69,Then will we take forth from each band those of them who have been stoutest in rebellion against the God of Mercy
  19,70,Then shall we know right well to whom its burning is most due
  19,71,No one is there of you who shall not go down unto it - This is a settled decree with thy Lord
  19,72,"Then will we deliver those who had the fear of God, and the wicked will we leave in it on their knees"
  19,73,"And when our clear signs are rehearsed to them, the infidels say to those who believe: \"Which of the two parties is in the best plight? and which is the most goodly company"
  19,74,"But how many generations have we brought to ruin before them, who surpassed them in riches and in splendour"
  19,75,"SAY: As to those who are in error, the God of Mercy will lengthen out to them a length of days Until they see that with which they are threatened, whether it be some present chastisement, or whether it be \"the Hour,\" and they shall then know which is in the worse state, and which the more weak in forces"
  19,76,"But God will increase the guidance of the already guided. And good works which abide, are in thy Lord's sight better in respect of guerdon, and better in the issue than all worldly good"